<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11003e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11003e">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11003e"> 3(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">C</font> born at midnight</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The same idea this as when the Chief, desiring to let me know I was very clever, said, pointing to the solar angle, &ldquo;Yes, you were born at half-past seven in the morning!&rdquo; a dense negro being told that he was <mark>born at twelve o&apos;clock midnight</mark>. <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB2"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 395</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c04029i" href="c4all.htm#c04029i">VI.C.04:029(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
